<TITLE> Campaigns, meetings stop from midnight </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 26 (bdnews24.com)  With campaigning to end from Saturday midnight, the Election Commission has also slapped bans on movement of transport ahead of the general election on Dec. 29. The EC in a statement said bans on processions, meetings and rallies in the electoral areas will remain in force for the next 48 hours after the vote. Buses, trucks, CNG-run auto-rickshaws, microbus, pick-ups, jeeps, taxicabs, auto rickshaws, engine-driven river vessels and speedboats will face restrictions on movements on the highways and riverways, said the EC in another statement. However, the metropolitan areas will remain beyond the ban except for taxicabs, microbuses, jeeps and pick-ups which will not be allowed on the streets. Public relations officer of the EC SM Asaduzzaman told bdnews24.com buses leaving the capital city will face no bar. The engine-driven river vessels also will not face any bar in the shoals and river areas in the country. Bans on motorcycle movement will stay effective from Dec. 27 midnight to Dec. 31. The ban may be relaxed for candidates and their polling agents, and in ports for urgent needs on permission from returning officers. The statement added local and overseas election observers, journalists, election officials and staffers, security forces and electoral inspectors will remain beyond the restrictions. Ambulances, and vehicles of utility services such as power, post, gas and telecommunication will be allowed to run during the ban, it said. bd
